        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 15 at 1:56PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 156 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Opelika. This thunderstorm was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Auburn, Opelika, Waverly, Sturkie, Oak Bowery, Auburn University,
Loachapoka, Robert G. Pitts Airport, Chewacla State Park, Roxana, and
Mount Jefferson.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
